HEADWORD: Matchless
<hw>Match"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Mateless</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Having no equal; unequaled.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A
<xex>matchless</xex> queen.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Waller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Unlike each other; unequal; unsuited.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Matchless</xex> ears.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Match"less*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Match"less*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
